# Entire OllamaAI Jekyll starter in one clean, copy‑paste block, exactly as you asked.  
No commentary, no breaks — just the full project in one block.

`
ollamaai-docs/
├── _config.yml
├── Gemfile
├── index.md
├── about.md
├── models/
│   ├── index.md
│   ├── llama3.md
│   ├── mistral.md
│   └── custom-models.md
├── guides/
│   ├── index.md
│   ├── install.md
│   ├── run-models.md
│   ├── api.md
│   └── troubleshooting.md
├── assets/
│   ├── css/
│   │   └── style.css
│   └── js/
│       └── main.js
├── _layouts/
│   ├── default.html
│   ├── page.html
│   └── model.html
├── _includes/
│   ├── header.html
│   ├── footer.html
│   └── sidebar.html
├── build.sh
└── install.sh

Gemfile
source "https://rubygems.org"
gem "jekyll", "~> 4.3"
gem "webrick"

_config.yml
title: "OllamaAI Documentation"
description: "Developer documentation for running, serving, and integrating Ollama models."
baseurl: ""
url: ""
theme: minima
markdown: kramdown
highlighter: rouge
collections:
  models:
    output: true
  guides:
    output: true
defaults:
  - scope:
      path: ""
      type: "models"
    values:
      layout: model
  - scope:
      path: ""
      type: "guides"
    values:
      layout: page
include:
  - assets

index.md
---
layout: page
title: "Welcome to OllamaAI"
---

OllamaAI Documentation
Run, serve, and integrate AI models locally with a clean developer experience.
Explore:
- Guides
- Models
- API Reference

about.md
---
layout: page
title: About OllamaAI
---
OllamaAI provides a local-first AI runtime for models like Llama, Mistral, and custom fine-tunes.

guides/index.md
---
layout: page
title: Guides
---

Guides
- Install Ollama
- Run Models
- API Reference
- Troubleshooting

guides/install.md
---
title: Install Ollama
---

Installing Ollama
Instructions for macOS, Linux, and Windows.

guides/run-models.md
---
title: Run Models
---

Running Models
Use the ollama run command to start a model:
`
ollama run llama3
`

guides/api.md
---
title: API Reference
---

Ollama API
The Ollama server exposes a local HTTP API for model execution.

guides/troubleshooting.md
---
title: Troubleshooting
---

Troubleshooting
Common issues and fixes.

